news.title: Ghaziabad: GDA ready to hand over Indirapuram, but GMC won't take it until infra work is over
news.para: While the GDA says it is ready to hand over the township to the corporation, the GMC has contended that there are pending infrastructure development issues in the township and it can’t take over Indirapuram until they are resolved.

news.title: Pune civic body's gunthewari scheme off to slow start
news.para: BJP’s state president Chandrakant Patil said, “Regularisation charges for the proposals should be reduced. Relaxation is a must in the rules related to road widths to avail this scheme.”

news.title: Life Mission's final list extended again by Kerala government
news.para: ​​As per the latest order issued by the local self-government department (LSGD) on Friday, the finalization of the draft list (which was supposed to be published on Feb 28) has now been extended till April 16.

news.title: Centre won't include wrongly deleted Rajasthan PMAY-Gramin beneficiaries
news.para: In a letter written to the state on February 15, 2022, the ministry wrote, “Request cannot be agreed as the system rejects the beneficiaries on the basis of the records entered by the state at the time of Awaas+ survey.”

news.title: Chamarajanagar development body permitted to construct new layouts
news.para: The state government has given green signal to develop the new layout with modern facilities on a 50:50 partnership basis. This comes amid an unsuccessful attempt by its counterpart in Mysuru.

news.title: Guidebook on residential EV charging in Delhi to be launched on Monday
news.para: ​The document guides residential societies in understanding the importance of EV charging, details the processes involved in planning, installing and managing EV charging stations in the parking space of the societies, the statement on Sunday said.

news.title: Karnataka government plans new scheme to regularise revenue sites
news.para: Chief minister Basavaraj Bommai has held several rounds of talks with state urban department, rural development and panchayat raj, and BBMP officials regarding a scheme to regularise B khata sites in major municipal corporations.

news.title: Tamil Nadu RERA orders Marg Properties to refund homebuyers
news.para: The complaint pertains to delay in delivery of apartments to four homebuyers in a housing project at Kalavakkam in Thiruporur on the outskirts of the city, developed by Marg Properties Ltd.

news.title: Government scouts for chief of properties & monetisation officer for AIAHL
news.para: Air India, which was state-owned at that time, was acquired by Tatas in January this year. The non-core assets of Air India, including land and building, valued at Rs 14,718 crore are with AIAHL.

news.title: Supply of high-value properties rise as big families look to sell jointly-owned homes
news.para: "Covid-19 has brought a fair bit of uncertainty into people's lives. We see a keenness among families, especially the elderly, to formalise the distribution of assets to the next of kin, in their lifetime," said Amit Goyal, CEO of India Sotheby's International Realty.

news.title: Brigade Enterprises' sales bookings up 14% Rs 1,995 crore in Apr-Dec 2022
news.para: Out of the total sales bookings, the housing segment contributed Rs 1,957.4 crore, up 17 per cent from Rs 1,668.2 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Government aims to provide pakka houses: Andhra Pradesh housing minister
news.para: On the final day, Saturday, the minister visited the layouts in Chodavaram and Yelamanchili constituencies in the Visakhapatnam district.

news.title: Don't just file complaint, act against illegal buildings: Kolkata Mayor
news.para: Hakim received a call during the talk-to-mayor programme from a Beckbagan resident, who complained about an illegal construction. He also asked the concerned department to show-cause an official regarding this.

news.title: BMC is authorised to crack down on unsafe buildings: Bombay HC
news.para: “People losing lives in building collapses need to be completely obliterated. The right to livelihood, in our opinion, includes the right to live in safe building and houses,’’ said Chief Justice Dipankar Datta and Justice Girish Kulkarni.

news.title: No water for houses illegally connected to supply network: Mysuru civic body
news.para: The Mysuru City Corporation, which is affected by mounting water bill dues, has decided to launch a drive to disconnect 40,000 water connections that are drawn illegally. The water supply lines are drawn without adopting water meters, which is affecting MCC’s revenue.
